HEADWORD: Nordic
<hw>Nordic</hw> <pos>prop. adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>of or pertaining
to the inhabitants of Scandinavia; <as>as, <ex>Nordic</ex> languages
have a gender system</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Relating to Germany and Scandinavia; <as>as, Hitler
wanted <ex>Nordic</ex> people to rule Europe</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Resembling the peoples of Scandinavia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

